1
00:01:11,360 --> 00:01:12,080
I like you.

2
00:02:47,880 --> 00:02:48,880
See you tomorrow.

3
00:02:53,600 --> 00:02:54,600
See you tomorrow.

4
00:04:10,520 --> 00:04:12,450
So he didn't say anything that day.

5
00:04:14,200 --> 00:04:16,000
I'm not sure if he heard me.

6
00:04:16,640 --> 00:04:18,000
Because he didn't say anything

7
00:04:18,000 --> 00:04:19,200
and just took me home.

8
00:04:21,079 --> 00:04:21,610
Xiaocen.

9
00:04:22,000 --> 00:04:23,000
You're amazing.

10
00:04:23,800 --> 00:04:25,260
You just said it like that.

11
00:04:25,800 --> 00:04:28,000
Didn't you tell me to be more proactive?

12
00:04:28,240 --> 00:04:29,500
Alright, don't worry.

13
00:04:30,080 --> 00:04:32,200
Xu Xiao might just be hesitating.

14
00:04:33,040 --> 00:04:34,370
Hesitating about what?

15
00:04:35,360 --> 00:04:36,400
I mean,

16
00:04:37,120 --> 00:04:38,520
he's just processing it.

17
00:04:41,720 --> 00:04:43,360
I really don't know what to do.

18
00:04:43,360 --> 00:04:44,760
It's fine, Xiaocen.

19
00:04:44,920 --> 00:04:45,600
Let me tell you.

20
00:04:45,600 --> 00:04:46,800
If I were Xu Xiao,

21
00:04:46,800 --> 00:04:49,600
I would have definitely said yes to you that night.

22
00:04:51,600 --> 00:04:52,600
Is it possible

23
00:04:52,600 --> 00:04:53,930
that he didn't hear you?

24
00:04:54,480 --> 00:04:55,880
If he didn't hear you,

25
00:04:56,120 --> 00:04:57,200
just say it again.

26
00:04:57,400 --> 00:04:59,040
Since you've already said it once,

27
00:04:59,040 --> 00:05:01,100
saying it a hundred times is the same.

28
00:05:01,480 --> 00:05:02,810
I'm not saying it again.

29
00:05:02,920 --> 00:05:03,400
Come on.

30
00:05:03,680 --> 00:05:04,680
Look into my eyes.

31
00:05:05,360 --> 00:05:05,820
Xu Xiao,

32
00:05:06,200 --> 00:05:07,040
I like you.

33
00:05:08,680 --> 00:05:10,120
Yuexin.

34
00:05:10,240 --> 00:05:11,480
You can do it, Xiaocen.

35
00:05:11,480 --> 00:05:12,600
I can't.

36
00:05:12,800 --> 00:05:13,680
You can.

37
00:05:19,200 --> 00:05:20,680
Um, Zhuoting,

38
00:05:21,600 --> 00:05:22,930
can I ask you something?

39
00:05:23,200 --> 00:05:23,730
Go ahead.

40
00:05:24,360 --> 00:05:26,220
When you and Xiaoyi got together,

41
00:05:26,520 --> 00:05:27,720
did you confess first,

42
00:05:27,720 --> 00:05:28,720
or did she?

43
00:05:29,080 --> 00:05:30,320
Of course I did.

44
00:05:30,440 --> 00:05:32,700
How could I let a girl make the first move?

45
00:05:34,560 --> 00:05:36,520
Why the sudden question?

46
00:05:39,800 --> 00:05:40,280
If...

47
00:05:40,480 --> 00:05:41,880
I mean, hypothetically,

48
00:05:42,720 --> 00:05:44,180
if Xiaoyi confessed to you

49
00:05:44,640 --> 00:05:46,700
and you didn't respond immediately,

50
00:05:46,880 --> 00:05:47,800
what would happen?

51
00:05:47,800 --> 00:05:49,460
Then we'd definitely be over.

52
00:05:49,520 --> 00:05:51,520
If I didn't give her a direct answer,

53
00:05:52,000 --> 00:05:53,530
she would probably hate me.

54
00:05:55,440 --> 00:05:55,880
Xu...

55
00:05:55,880 --> 00:05:56,560
Xu Xiao.

56
00:05:57,520 --> 00:05:59,120
Why are you suddenly asking me

57
00:05:59,120 --> 00:06:00,520
such a private question?

58
00:06:01,400 --> 00:06:02,130
Just asking.

59
00:06:05,360 --> 00:06:06,880
Is there something going on with you?

60
00:06:06,880 --> 00:06:07,320
No.

61
00:06:07,640 --> 00:06:08,840
Don't talk nonsense.

62
00:06:09,360 --> 00:06:10,600
Does it have to do with Zhao Xiaocen?

63
00:06:10,600 --> 00:06:11,040
No.

64
00:06:16,640 --> 00:06:17,700
One more question.

65
00:06:18,920 --> 00:06:19,520
Do you and Xiaoyi

66
00:06:19,520 --> 00:06:21,840
usually go anywhere romantic?

67
00:06:23,000 --> 00:06:26,000
We usually just walk around the market

68
00:06:26,280 --> 00:06:28,000
and grab a bite to eat or something.

69
00:06:28,000 --> 00:06:28,600
Oh, right.

70
00:06:28,840 --> 00:06:29,920
There's a music bar

71
00:06:30,360 --> 00:06:31,760
that's really romantic.

72
00:06:33,280 --> 00:06:34,409
Send me the address.

73
00:06:36,360 --> 00:06:38,159
I knew something was up with you.

74
00:06:38,280 --> 00:06:40,140
You have to tell me what it's about

75
00:06:40,320 --> 00:06:41,400
before I tell you.

76
00:06:47,480 --> 00:06:49,159
I solemnly request

77
00:06:49,760 --> 00:06:51,360
that you send me the address.

78
00:07:07,400 --> 00:07:08,260
I sent it to you.

79
00:07:10,480 --> 00:07:11,000
Thanks.

80
00:07:11,720 --> 00:07:12,650
I'm leaving now.

81
00:07:17,560 --> 00:07:18,490
I've scanned it.

82
00:07:18,520 --> 00:07:19,120
Thank you.

83
00:07:42,880 --> 00:07:43,740
Do you have time

84
00:07:45,520 --> 00:07:46,159
tonight?

85
00:07:48,040 --> 00:07:48,800
Yes.

86
00:07:49,680 --> 00:07:51,210
I'll send you the location.

87
00:07:52,280 --> 00:07:52,840
Okay.

88
00:08:23,200 --> 00:08:24,880
I'm an hour early.

89
00:08:26,840 --> 00:08:28,040
So early.

90
00:08:36,600 --> 00:08:37,159
Hello.

91
00:08:37,559 --> 00:08:38,080
Hello.

92
00:08:40,400 --> 00:08:41,520
Can I help you?

93
00:08:41,880 --> 00:08:43,559
Excuse me, where is seat three?

94
00:08:43,559 --> 00:08:44,360
It's this way.

95
00:08:45,000 --> 00:08:45,800
Okay, thanks.

96
00:08:45,880 --> 00:08:46,810
You're welcome.

97
00:09:23,000 --> 00:09:23,440
Hello?

98
00:09:23,920 --> 00:09:24,560
Hello?

99
00:09:25,640 --> 00:09:26,440
Where are you?

100
00:09:28,560 --> 00:09:30,480
Isn't it at eight? I'm at home.

101
00:09:32,920 --> 00:09:33,920
I was just asking.

102
00:09:35,720 --> 00:09:36,780
It's fine. No rush.

103
00:09:37,680 --> 00:09:38,600
That shop

104
00:09:38,920 --> 00:09:40,050
is a bit hard to find.

105
00:09:40,600 --> 00:09:42,160
I haven't left yet anyway.

106
00:09:43,320 --> 00:09:44,120
Where are you?

107
00:09:45,080 --> 00:09:46,410
I'm at the antique shop.

108
00:09:47,400 --> 00:09:48,660
I'll head over in a bit.

109
00:09:49,240 --> 00:09:49,760
Okay.

110
00:09:51,680 --> 00:09:53,400
See you in a bit then.

111
00:09:53,880 --> 00:09:54,680
See you later.

112
00:11:01,320 --> 00:11:01,720
Hello.

113
00:11:02,040 --> 00:11:02,680
Hello?

114
00:11:03,560 --> 00:11:04,360
Where are you?

115
00:11:05,200 --> 00:11:06,000
I'm almost there.

116
00:11:06,000 --> 00:11:06,800
I'm at that...

117
00:11:08,080 --> 00:11:10,520
I'm outside that white coffee shop.

118
00:11:10,600 --> 00:11:11,730
I'll be right there.

119
00:11:12,120 --> 00:11:13,250
I know where you are.

120
00:11:13,400 --> 00:11:14,330
I'll come to you.

121
00:11:14,960 --> 00:11:15,760
Wait a moment.

122
00:11:39,920 --> 00:11:40,240
I,

123
00:11:40,640 --> 00:11:41,560
I've arrived.

124
00:11:42,360 --> 00:11:43,160
Where are you?

125
00:11:43,360 --> 00:11:43,960
Here.

126
00:11:44,360 --> 00:11:45,020
Right here.

127
00:11:45,120 --> 00:11:45,800
I'm here.

128
00:11:49,960 --> 00:11:50,820
I just got here.

129
00:11:52,160 --> 00:11:53,690
How long have you been here?

130
00:11:55,960 --> 00:11:57,020
I just got here too.

131
00:12:00,200 --> 00:12:01,130
It's over there.

132
00:12:01,160 --> 00:12:01,690
Let's go.

133
00:12:01,720 --> 00:12:02,360
Okay.

134
00:12:17,480 --> 00:12:18,880
It's pretty good, right?

135
00:12:19,280 --> 00:12:19,680
Here.

136
00:12:33,680 --> 00:12:34,640
It sounds nice.

137
00:12:37,440 --> 00:12:37,920
Okay.

138
00:12:39,000 --> 00:12:39,440
Hello.

139
00:12:39,760 --> 00:12:40,160
Hello.

140
00:12:40,640 --> 00:12:41,360
Here are your drinks.

141
00:12:41,360 --> 00:12:41,960
Thank you.

142
00:12:43,320 --> 00:12:44,450
That's everything.

143
00:13:30,520 --> 00:13:32,120
Actually, when I was little,

144
00:13:33,920 --> 00:13:35,650
right after my dad's accident,

145
00:13:37,840 --> 00:13:39,200
for a very long time,

146
00:13:40,560 --> 00:13:41,890
I became very negative.

147
00:13:43,760 --> 00:13:45,560
Because many kids in my class...

148
00:13:46,320 --> 00:13:49,180
We're all kids from Jingdezhen ceramics families.

149
00:13:50,520 --> 00:13:51,320
Their parents

150
00:13:52,440 --> 00:13:54,640
would deliberately make them avoid me.

151
00:13:57,200 --> 00:13:57,800
My dad

152
00:13:58,920 --> 00:14:01,050
didn't want to see his friends either.

153
00:14:02,680 --> 00:14:04,210
So every time after school,

154
00:14:05,560 --> 00:14:08,090
I had to wait at the school gate for a long time.

155
00:14:09,960 --> 00:14:11,360
I waited until those kids

156
00:14:11,920 --> 00:14:13,720
were picked up by their parents.

157
00:14:14,640 --> 00:14:16,400
Only then would my dad show up to pick me up.

158
00:14:16,400 --> 00:14:16,800
Xiao,

159
00:14:17,320 --> 00:14:18,850
Daddy's here to pick you up.

160
00:14:21,440 --> 00:14:21,840
Xiao.

161
00:14:30,000 --> 00:14:30,960
Since then,

162
00:14:32,920 --> 00:14:34,580
I've been used to being alone,

163
00:14:36,200 --> 00:14:38,000
and doing everything by myself.

164
00:14:39,680 --> 00:14:41,200
I'm used to expecting the worst

165
00:14:41,200 --> 00:14:42,600
in everything.

166
00:14:45,320 --> 00:14:46,720
So no matter the outcome,

167
00:14:50,480 --> 00:14:52,280
I wouldn't be too disappointed.

168
00:14:55,680 --> 00:14:57,080
What you said last night,

169
00:14:58,600 --> 00:14:59,200
I heard it.

170
00:15:06,840 --> 00:15:08,040
I didn't dare to think

171
00:15:09,680 --> 00:15:12,010
such a wonderful thing would happen to me.

172
00:15:16,480 --> 00:15:17,410
I didn't believe

173
00:15:19,200 --> 00:15:21,800
the person I care about would care about me too.

174
00:15:33,360 --> 00:15:35,490
But this time, I don't want to run away.

175
00:15:36,880 --> 00:15:38,010
I want to be like you,

176
00:15:39,560 --> 00:15:40,760
and be brave for once.

177
00:15:47,720 --> 00:15:48,320
Xiaocen.

178
00:15:51,080 --> 00:15:51,800
I like you.

179
00:17:21,040 --> 00:17:21,880
We

180
00:17:22,960 --> 00:17:24,160
are together now.

181
00:17:47,080 --> 00:17:47,720
Xu Xiao.

182
00:17:48,080 --> 00:17:49,040
What are these?

183
00:17:49,600 --> 00:17:50,240
These

184
00:17:50,760 --> 00:17:51,920
were from former JCU seniors

185
00:17:51,920 --> 00:17:52,850
who told me about

186
00:17:53,080 --> 00:17:54,740
this custom they left behind.

187
00:17:55,320 --> 00:17:57,040
People hang what they want to say

188
00:17:57,040 --> 00:17:58,680
and the things they want to leave behind

189
00:17:58,680 --> 00:17:59,480
on the tree.

190
00:18:04,960 --> 00:18:07,020
When I was little, I never understood

191
00:18:07,040 --> 00:18:07,880
why my parents

192
00:18:07,880 --> 00:18:09,610
always made me clean the house.

193
00:18:10,120 --> 00:18:11,640
It turns out that when the house is messy,

194
00:18:11,640 --> 00:18:13,240
your mind is truly messy too.

195
00:18:15,960 --> 00:18:17,020
What did you write?

196
00:18:18,080 --> 00:18:20,240
I bit my nails off

197
00:18:20,440 --> 00:18:22,170
and want to get them done again.

198
00:18:56,840 --> 00:18:57,570
What is this?

199
00:18:58,880 --> 00:18:59,680
A leaf.

200
00:19:02,640 --> 00:19:04,570
A butterfly. It feels so familiar,

201
00:19:05,000 --> 00:19:05,860
yet so distant.

202
00:19:06,800 --> 00:19:09,000
This is the moment I drew.

203
00:19:09,560 --> 00:19:11,040
Do you recognize it?

204
00:19:23,160 --> 00:19:24,890
Have you ever thought about it?

205
00:19:25,120 --> 00:19:26,720
If you could leave a sentence

206
00:19:27,040 --> 00:19:28,080
or an item behind,

207
00:19:29,280 --> 00:19:30,480
what would you leave?

208
00:19:35,800 --> 00:19:38,000
I don't think I've thought about it yet.

209
00:19:40,640 --> 00:19:41,680
But I believe

210
00:19:42,560 --> 00:19:43,620
what I leave behind

211
00:19:44,560 --> 00:19:47,220
will definitely be the most worthwhile things.

212
00:19:55,480 --> 00:19:57,560
Jing and the others are live streaming,

213
00:19:57,560 --> 00:19:59,420
setting up a stall at Taoxichuan.

214
00:19:59,560 --> 00:20:01,820
Look, there are more people than before.

215
00:20:02,120 --> 00:20:03,480
Xiaocen, look at this.

216
00:20:07,920 --> 00:20:08,600
Xu Xiao.

217
00:20:09,040 --> 00:20:10,080
What a coincidence.

218
00:20:10,080 --> 00:20:11,400
You guys are shopping too?

219
00:20:11,400 --> 00:20:11,800
Yeah.

220
00:20:12,120 --> 00:20:13,450
Are you shopping alone?

221
00:20:15,400 --> 00:20:15,840
Alone.

222
00:20:16,560 --> 00:20:17,960
Sometimes I come alone.

223
00:20:22,640 --> 00:20:23,700
Women's clothing.

224
00:20:24,840 --> 00:20:25,400
Just looking at clothes.

225
00:20:25,400 --> 00:20:26,160
Xu Xiao.

226
00:20:26,560 --> 00:20:27,560
Actually, the boys in our class

227
00:20:27,560 --> 00:20:29,160
all want to hang out with you.

228
00:20:29,400 --> 00:20:31,520
You don't have to be alone all the time.

229
00:20:31,520 --> 00:20:32,520
Alright, Xiaoyi.

230
00:20:32,640 --> 00:20:34,040
Let's not disturb Xu Xiao

231
00:20:34,360 --> 00:20:35,560
while he looks at clothes alone.

232
00:20:35,560 --> 00:20:36,090
Let's go.

233
00:20:36,720 --> 00:20:37,440
Bye.

234
00:20:49,120 --> 00:20:50,120
Sorry.

235
00:20:50,400 --> 00:20:52,330
Actually, you didn't have to hide.

236
00:20:53,760 --> 00:20:54,960
It's just that

237
00:20:55,640 --> 00:20:57,880
I don't really know how to face them

238
00:20:57,880 --> 00:20:58,600
if they found out.

239
00:20:58,600 --> 00:20:59,200
It's fine.

240
00:20:59,640 --> 00:21:00,100
I get it.

241
00:21:02,960 --> 00:21:03,490
Let's go.

242
00:21:25,840 --> 00:21:27,120
Mom, I'm not eating.

243
00:21:27,120 --> 00:21:28,280
My classmate is waiting for me.

244
00:21:28,280 --> 00:21:29,080
Wait a minute.

245
00:21:29,120 --> 00:21:31,000
Didn't you say you wanted rice noodles yesterday?

246
00:21:31,000 --> 00:21:32,640
Mom bought it for you early in the morning.

247
00:21:32,640 --> 00:21:33,720
I made plans with my classmates.

248
00:21:33,720 --> 00:21:34,760
We are having a big pizza today.

249
00:21:34,760 --> 00:21:35,490
I'm leaving.

250
00:21:38,320 --> 00:21:39,200
Slow down.

251
00:21:40,200 --> 00:21:41,440
Auntie.

252
00:21:42,440 --> 00:21:43,120
I want some.

253
00:21:43,600 --> 00:21:44,400
Come quickly.

254
00:21:50,440 --> 00:21:51,360
Taste it and see if you like it.

255
00:21:51,360 --> 00:21:51,680
Okay.

256
00:21:51,680 --> 00:21:53,140
Put down your chopsticks.

257
00:21:55,960 --> 00:21:58,600
Have your millet porridge. It's good for your stomach.

258
00:21:58,600 --> 00:22:00,680
Look at this, too much oil and chili.

259
00:22:00,680 --> 00:22:01,760
Your stomach can't handle it,

260
00:22:01,760 --> 00:22:02,820
so you can't eat it.

261
00:22:05,000 --> 00:22:05,920
Sis.

262
00:22:06,200 --> 00:22:08,720
Aren't you tired of millet porridge every day?

263
00:22:08,720 --> 00:22:10,560
What's wrong with having a taste occasionally?

264
00:22:10,560 --> 00:22:11,040
Here.

265
00:22:11,280 --> 00:22:12,440
This is Jiangxi.

266
00:22:12,640 --> 00:22:14,160
She finally got into a university here.

267
00:22:14,160 --> 00:22:15,000
She should experience

268
00:22:15,000 --> 00:22:16,330
the local food and life.

269
00:22:18,600 --> 00:22:19,600
Let me tell you,

270
00:22:19,680 --> 00:22:21,520
of course we have to watch what she eats.

271
00:22:21,520 --> 00:22:22,600
You spoil Xing.

272
00:22:22,920 --> 00:22:23,400
Look at her.

273
00:22:23,400 --> 00:22:24,160
One day she wants this,

274
00:22:24,160 --> 00:22:24,840
the next day she wants that.

275
00:22:24,840 --> 00:22:26,000
Pizzas, hamburgers.

276
00:22:26,000 --> 00:22:27,040
They're so unnutritious.

277
00:22:27,040 --> 00:22:28,520
You really can't raise a child like this.

278
00:22:28,520 --> 00:22:30,080
You can't get better.

279
00:22:30,840 --> 00:22:32,480
Don't waste this. I'll eat it for lunch.

280
00:22:32,480 --> 00:22:33,720
Sister, let me eat it.

281
00:22:34,320 --> 00:22:35,320
No need.

282
00:22:35,320 --> 00:22:36,400
I'll eat it.

283
00:22:43,240 --> 00:22:45,370
Mom, I'm going to be late. I'm leaving.

284
00:22:47,160 --> 00:22:48,760
You finished eating so fast.

285
00:22:48,840 --> 00:22:49,720
Wait a minute.

286
00:22:50,360 --> 00:22:51,160
Wait a minute.

287
00:22:51,520 --> 00:22:52,080
Cup.

288
00:22:52,520 --> 00:22:52,920
Here.

289
00:22:53,880 --> 00:22:55,040
Alright, it's packed.

290
00:22:55,040 --> 00:22:57,040
Remember to drink water, it's too hot.

291
00:22:57,040 --> 00:22:57,920
Be careful of the heat.

292
00:22:57,920 --> 00:22:58,760
Got it.

293
00:23:11,240 --> 00:23:12,640
I brought you breakfast.

294
00:23:14,360 --> 00:23:14,960
Jiaoziba.

295
00:23:16,000 --> 00:23:16,640
Thank you.

296
00:23:17,160 --> 00:23:18,690
